Sleep Pattern App (JSON Storage)

This version stores app data in a backend JSON file so it persists across browsers.

Why you must run it this way:
Opening the HTML file directly skips the backend, so the app cannot read/write the shared JSON file. Running via http://localhost:3000 ensures all browsers use the same backend and data file.

Run the app
1. Open a terminal in this folder.
2. Install dependencies:
	npm install
3. Start the server:
	npm start
4. Open in your browser:
	http://localhost:3000

API endpoints
- GET /api/data   -> loads persisted state
- POST /api/data  -> saves full state snapshot

Persistence file
- data.json (created automatically on first run)

